items.title: Rheinmetall chief says Europe must catch up with Russia's ammunition output as it opens mega plant
items.description: The company's new plant in Northern Germany is set to become Europe's biggest ammunition production facility.

items.title: Researcher who has distorted voter data appointed to Homeland Security election integrity role
items.description: Heather Honey, a conservative election researcher, was appointed to the new role amid Trump's push to restructure how elections are run.

items.title: Feds fail to get indictment against DC 'Subway' sandwich thrower who DOJ fired
items.description: Sean Charles Dunn was fired from his job at the Department of Justice after the sub-chucking incident, which was caught on video.

items.title: Two children dead, 17 people injured in Annunciation school shooting: Minneapolis police
items.description: President Donald Trump spoke to Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz about the Annunciation school shooting, the White House said.
